--multiline -U # Multi-line matching

Using that approach, '.' does not match '\n'. To fix that, you can either:
 - Use '--multiline-dotall'
 - use the regex "dot all" modifier: "(?s)theActualRegexMatch"

# start detached

-l, --files-with-matches

-v, invert match?

iglob
